02:19:19.200 --> 02:19:21.190
of them represented here

02:19:21.190 --> 02:19:21.200
tonight—we

02:19:21.200 --> 02:19:23.030
pray for their families. We

02:19:23.040 --> 02:19:24.790
pray for them, Father. We thank You,

02:19:24.800 --> 02:19:27.190
Lord, for the glory of the Lord in the

02:19:27.200 --> 02:19:29.589
name of Jesus that surrounds them. As

02:19:29.599 --> 02:19:31.509
we continue to pray and lift up the

02:19:31.519 --> 02:19:33.429
nations together, we give You

02:19:33.439 --> 02:19:35.270
praise, Lord. Amen and amen.

02:19:35.280 --> 02:19:37.270
And for the people who have droughts, we

02:19:37.280 --> 02:19:38.150
pray for rain.

02:19:38.160 --> 02:19:39.830
We call in rain.

02:19:39.840 --> 02:19:41.110
I don't know why I just thought of that.

02:19:41.120 --> 02:19:42.950
Yeah, we call in rain. We call in rain.

02:19:42.960 --> 02:19:44.870
We call five inches for every

02:19:44.880 --> 02:19:47.349
single one of you—five inches of rain

02:19:47.359 --> 02:19:49.510
on every single household in the name of

02:19:49.520 --> 02:19:51.910
Jesus. That it would be such a bountiful

02:19:51.920 --> 02:19:53.750
supply that it would be a

02:19:53.750 --> 02:19:53.760
toad-strangler.

02:19:53.760 --> 02:19:56.710
Father, I thank You,

02:19:56.720 --> 02:19:58.950
Lord, that You're bringing in the rain on

02:19:58.960 --> 02:20:01.590
the currents all around. Father, that we

02:20:01.600 --> 02:20:04.389
break drought in Jesus'name. We come

02:20:04.399 --> 02:20:07.990
against drought. We say, 'Drought, go in

02:20:07.990 --> 02:20:08.000
Jesus'name.

02:20:08.000 --> 02:20:11.670
Rain, come in

02:20:11.670 --> 02:20:11.680
Jesus'name.'And

02:20:11.680 --> 02:20:14.070
we thank You, Father, for the Holy

02:20:14.080 --> 02:20:17.429
Ghost flow of rain, rain, rain

02:20:17.439 --> 02:20:20.309
over our earth. Water our fields. Water

02:20:20.319 --> 02:20:22.389
our streams. Water our trees and our

02:20:22.399 --> 02:20:24.230
grass. Father, we thank You, Lord. Thank

02:20:24.240 --> 02:20:25.750
You for the rain we received tonight,

02:20:25.760 --> 02:20:27.510
Lord. Thank You for the thunder. Thank

02:20:27.520 --> 02:20:28.870
You for the lightning. Thank You for the

02:20:28.880 --> 02:20:31.750
blessing. Cleaning our air, cleaning

02:20:31.760 --> 02:20:33.750
things, getting ready for

02:20:33.760 --> 02:20:39.910
a beautiful summer that's coming.

02:20:46.560 --> 02:20:48.550
I know it's been a long

02:20:48.560 --> 02:20:50.710
time. We'll pray again tomorrow, but I

02:20:50.720 --> 02:20:53.110
just pause because I'm trying to

02:20:53.120 --> 02:20:54.710
filter

02:20:54.720 --> 02:21:00.389
as we grow.

02:21:00.399 --> 02:21:01.670
I thought it was great.

02:21:01.680 --> 02:21:02.230
You did?

02:21:02.240 --> 02:21:04.230
Yeah, I thought it was wonderful.

02:21:04.240 --> 02:21:05.110
Okay.

02:21:05.120 --> 02:21:06.550
Well, you're always there for me, honey.

02:21:06.560 --> 02:21:09.910
I want to get to that

02:21:09.920 --> 02:21:12.309
level when you're praying and

02:21:12.319 --> 02:21:14.630
I'm seeing over what I'm seeing, and I

02:21:14.640 --> 02:21:14.870
don't know.

02:21:14.880 --> 02:21:18.309
I felt the flow when I was in

02:21:18.319 --> 02:21:19.030
the river.

02:21:19.040 --> 02:21:21.110
All right. Well, we love you. Put a

02:21:21.120 --> 02:21:22.630
smile on your face and a song in your

02:21:22.640 --> 02:21:24.389
heart. We'll see you tomorrow. God bless

02:21:24.399 --> 02:21:25.990
you all. Have a wonderful night. Bye-bye.

